headline: Americans Are Abandoning Dreams of Home Ownership, Retirement
summary: Americans are running faster and faster toward their financial goals, but many feel like they’re spinning on a hamster wheel.  Across age ranges, roughly 90% of Americans are anxious broader economic forces will impact their long-term financial plans, according to U.S. Bank’s latest wealth survey.  Eight in 10 of the 5,000 people surveyed said they feel anxious about stock market fluctuations.
